 East London - The first citizen of the Buffalo City Metro, Executive Mayor Xola Pakati led by example and took the first corona virus test in the City on Tuesday morning. The Department of Health kicked off the COVID 19 public screening and testing campaign at the Gonubie Kings Mall taxi rank. “Even though I am not showing any symptoms, I think it’s important for people to understand that they should volunteer to be screened and tested if needs be, “ said Executive Mayor Pakati. The Department of Health will conduct screening and testing throughout the City. The campaign will focus on: *Test all close contacts of the index cases (confirmed positive COVID 19) within a house hold.*Screen everyone in the identified hotspot areas within communities and test all persons presenting with a minimum of 2 symptoms of COVID-19*All staff members in the PHC facilities, employees of staff in the garages, police station and shops within the malls in the identified hot spot areas will be tested. It will focus on the following areas: COASTAL AREAS Gonubie & Mzamomhle, 7/4/20Beacon Bay and NompumeleloEast London correctional services Duncan 8/4/20Village/Gompo areas 9/4/20 MIDLAND AREAS Mdantsane NU8 and Unit P 14/4/20Nxamkwana Iocation next to Pottsdam 14/4/20Reeston & Ducats 15/4/20 INLAND AREAS Amajarantina & llitha 16/4/20Pollar Park (Dimbaza) 17/4/20 Ncera and Chalumna 21/4/20Zwelitsha and Sweetwaters 22/4/20 Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 